article.description: — Noah Freidel scored 13 points as James Madison beat South Dakota State 79-60 on Saturday.
article.headline: Freidel's 13 help James Madison take down South Dakota State
article.linkText: Freidel's 13 help James Madison take down South Dakota State
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. -- — Noah Freidel scored 13 points as James Madison beat South Dakota State 79-60 on Saturday. Freidel was 5 of 13 shooting (3 for 8 from distance) for the Dukes (6-1). Alonzo Sule scored 11 points and added seven rebounds. Mezie Offurum shot 4 of 8 from the field and 2 for 3 from the line to finish with 10 points. Zeke Mayo finished with 16 points for the Jackrabbits (3-4). William Kyle III added 15 points, seven rebounds and two blocks for South Dakota State. In addition, Charlie Easley finished with 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
